data("ceosal1")

## Type: OLS linear regression 
## 
## MODEL FIT:
## F(1,207) = 2.77, p = 0.10
## R² = 0.01
## Adj. R² = 0.01 
## 
## Standard errors: OLS
## ---------------------------------------------------
##                       Est.     S.E.   t val.      p
## ----------------- -------- -------- -------- ------
## (Intercept)         963.19   213.24     4.52   0.00
## roe                  18.50    11.12     1.66   0.10
## ---------------------------------------------------
ggplot(ceosal1, aes(roe, salary)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(method = "lm")

#1
X <- runif(10000, 0, 10)
mean(X)
## [1] 5.000131
sd(X)
## [1] 2.905243
#2
u <- rnorm(10000, 0, 6)
mean(u)
## [1] 0.01961642
sd(u)
## [1] 5.974645
#3
Y <- 1 + 2 * X + u
summ(lm(Y ~ X))
## MODEL INFO:
## Observations: 10000
## Dependent Variable: Y
## Type: OLS linear regression 
## 
## MODEL FIT:
## F(1,9998) = 9648.11, p = 0.00
## R² = 0.49
## Adj. R² = 0.49 
## 
## Standard errors: OLS
## -----------------------------------------------
##                     Est.   S.E.   t val.      p

#4
round(sum(lm(Y ~ X)$residuals), 3)
## [1] 0
round(sum(X * lm(Y ~ X)$residuals), 3)

round(sum(u), 3)
